Spanjaard, Stratcorp, Taste, Zeder May Move: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-07-07T22:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/spanjaard-stratcorp-taste-zeder-may-move-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa  today. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index advanced to a more than
five-week high, gaining 165.36, or 0.5 percent, to 32,296.07 in
Johannesburg.  Spanjaard Ltd. (SPA)  : The distributor of lubricants and
chemical products holds its annual general meeting. The stock
was unchanged at 4.15 rand.  Stratcorp Ltd. (STA)  : The South African financial
services company holds its annual general meeting. Shares were
unchanged at 10 cents.  Taste Holdings Ltd. (TAS)  : The restaurant operator
transfers its listing from the AltX, the alternative exchange
for small and medium-size companies, to the main board of the
Johannesburg Stock Exchange, where it will be classified as a
retail company. The stock closed unchanged at 90 cents.  Zeder Investments Ltd. (ZED)  : The agricultural
investment group said it had acquired additional stock in
Capespan Group Ltd., taking its shareholding in the fruit
exporter to 36.1 percent and triggering a mandatory offer to
minority shareholders in the company. The stock fell 2 cents, or
0.8 percent, to 2.56 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  